(5960, 178, '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>Singapore to Develop Marine Tourism in Riau Islands of Indonesia</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Singapore has expressed its interest in developing marine tourism in Natuna, Anambas and Lingga, three beautiful yet hidden regencies in the Riau Islands province of Indonesia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to Riau Islands deputy Governor, Soeryo Respationo, the three areas have their own beauty but lack of adequate infrastructure to boost tourism.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Singapore&#39;s investment in the tourism sector would perfectly match with the islands&#39; need, he said recently. Soeryo said that Singapore Ambassador Anil Kumar Nayar visited the Riau islands asministration on Tuesday to show the country&#39;s commitment in developing the marine tourism sector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to the text above, Singapore is interested in making investment in .&hellip;</p>\r\n', 1, '', '<p>Tourism in the three islands in Riau</p>\r\n', '<p>Tourism in the sea around the three islands in Riau</p>\r\n', '<p>Building marine infrastructure in the three islands in Riau</p>\r\n', '<p>Building tourism infrastructure in the three islands in Riau</p>\r\n', '', 'opt4_soal', '', 1, 1),
(5961, 178, '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>Singapore to Develop Marine Tourism in Riau Islands of Indonesia</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Singapore has expressed its interest in developing marine tourism in Natuna, Anambas and Lingga, three beautiful yet hidden regencies in the Riau Islands province of Indonesia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to Riau Islands deputy Governor, Soeryo Respationo, the three areas have their own beauty but lack of adequate infrastructure to boost tourism.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Singapore&#39;s investment in the tourism sector would perfectly match with the islands&#39; need, he said recently. Soeryo said that Singapore Ambassador Anil Kumar Nayar visited the Riau islands asministration on Tuesday to show the country&#39;s commitment in developing the marine tourism sector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What is the main idea of paragraph 3?</p>\r\n', 1, '', '<p>Singapore shows its commitment in developing the marine tourism sector in the three islands in Riau</p>\r\n', '<p>Singapore ambassador visited the three islands in Riau</p>\r\n', '<p>Singapore needs to invest in the three islands in Riau</p>\r\n', '<p>Anil Kumar Nayar is the Singapore ambassador in Indonesia</p>\r\n', '', 'opt1_soal', '', 1, 1),
(5962, 178, '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>Singapore to Develop Marine Tourism in Riau Islands of Indonesia</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Singapore has expressed its interest in developing marine tourism in Natuna, Anambas and Lingga, three beautiful yet hidden regencies in the Riau Islands province of Indonesia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to Riau Islands deputy Governor, Soeryo Respationo, the three areas have their own beauty but lack of adequate infrastructure to boost tourism.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Singapore&#39;s investment in the tourism sector would perfectly match with the islands&#39; need, he said recently. Soeryo said that Singapore Ambassador Anil Kumar Nayar visited the Riau islands asministration on Tuesday to show the country&#39;s commitment in developing the marine tourism sector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;According to Riau Islands deputy Governor, Soeryo Respationo, the three areas have their own beauty but&hellip;&rdquo; (paragraph 2).<br />\r\nThe word &ldquo;their&rdquo; refers to &hellip;.</p>\r\n', 1, '', '<p>Natuna, Anambas, Lingga</p>\r\n', '<p>Anil Kumar Nayar&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Singapore</p>\r\n', '<p>The Island</p>\r\n', '', 'opt1_soal', '', 1, 1),
(5963, 178, '<p>nakes are reptiles (cold-blooded creatures). They belong to the same group as lizards (the scaled group, Squamata) but from a sub-group of their own (Serpentes).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Snakes have two legs but a long time ago they had claws to help them slither along. Snakes are not slimy. They are covered in scales which are just bumps on the skin. Their skin is hard and glossy to reduce friction as the snake slithers along the ground. Snakes often sun bathe on rocks in the warm weather. This is because snakes are cold-blooded; they need the sun&rsquo;s warmth to heat their bodies up. Most snakes live in the country. Some types of snakes live in tress, some live in water, but most live on the ground in deserted rabbit burrows, in thick, long grass and in old logs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A snake&rsquo;s diet usually consists of frogs, lizard, and mice and other snakes. The Anaconda can eat small crocodiles and even bears. Many snakes protect themselves with their fangs. Some snakes are protected by scaring their enemies away like the Cobra. The flying snakes glide away from danger. Their ribs spread apart and the skin stretches out. Its technique is just like the sugar gliders.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From the text we know that&hellip;.</p>\r\n', 1, '', '<p>Snakes do not have claws</p>\r\n', '<p>Snakes do not like sunlight</p>\r\n', '<p>Snakes use their legs to climb the tree</p>\r\n', '<p>Snakes use their claws to slither along the ground</p>\r\n', '', 'opt4_soal', '', 1, 1),
